        "body": "## Summary\n\n`gemini-3.5-flash` was missing from the bundled Google model catalog. Every sibling Gemini model ships with the correct 1,048,576-token context window, but `gemini-3.5-flash` silently fell back to the 200k `DEFAULT_CONTEXT_TOKENS` default.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/google/provider-catalog.ts`: Add `gemini-3.5-flash` entry with `contextWindow: 1_048_576` and `maxTokens: 65_536`\n- `extensions/google/provider-models.ts`: Add forward-compat routing prefix for `gemini-3.5-flash`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: gemini-3.5-flash silently used 200k context window instead of the documented 1M input window.\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-94723-gemini-3.5-flash-catalog.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n  npx tsx -e 'import { buildGoogleStaticCatalogProvider } from \"./extensions/google/provider-catalog.ts\"; ...'\n  node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/google/provider-catalog.test.ts extensions/google/provider-models.test.ts\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { buildGoogleStaticCatalogProvider } from \"./extensions/google/provider-catalog.ts\"; ...'\n\n=== Google provider catalog (gemini models excerpt) ===\n\n  google/gemini-2.5-pro\n    contextWindow: 1,048,576\n    maxTokens:    65,536\n\n  google/gemini-3.5-flash    <-- NEW entry, previously missing\n    contextWindow: 1,048,576\n    maxTokens:    65,536\n\n  google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview\n    contextWindow: 1,048,576\n    maxTokens:    65,536\n\n  google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite\n    contextWindow: 1,048,576\n    maxTokens:    65,536\n\n  google/gemini-3-flash-preview\n    contextWindow: 1,048,576\n    maxTokens:    65,536\n\n=> gemini-3.5-flash now resolves with correct 1,048,576 context window\n\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/google/provider-catalog.test.ts ...\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n ✓ 2 test files  |  25 tests passed\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The gemini-3.5-flash model now appears in the static Google provider catalog with the correct 1,048,576 context window, matching its documented capabilities and sibling models. All 25 Google provider tests pass.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a live Google API key (requires platform-specific credentials). The static catalog entry is a data addition—no runtime behavior change beyond resolving the correct context window.\n\nCloses: #94723",
